# Autodesk Assignment API
Live API on Heroku

## Live API Link
[Autodesk API on Heroku](https://autodesk-noam-d6347ff07cb2.herokuapp.com/)

## Documentation
### Endpoints:
#### Root Endpoint
URL: /
Description: Returns a simple greeting message from the API.
Method: GET

#### Search Endpoint
URL: /search
Description: Fetches Autodesk-related videos from YouTube API.
Method: GET

#### Health Check Endpoint
URL: /health
Description: Provides health status information about the server.
Method: GET

## How to Use:
Clone this repository to your local machine.
Install the required dependencies using npm install.
Set up your environment variables by creating a .env file based on the provided .env.example file and adding your YouTube API key.
Start the server by running npm start.
You can now access the API endpoints locally using the provided routes.

## Error Handling:
The API handles errors gracefully and returns appropriate error responses with status codes.
If you encounter any issues, refer to the error messages in the response for troubleshooting.

## Running Locally with Docker
To run the service locally with Docker, follow these steps:

Make sure you have Docker installed on your machine.
Clone this repository to your local machine.
Build the Docker image using the provided Dockerfile:
Copy code
docker build -t autodesk-assignment-api .
Run the Docker container:
arduino
Copy code
docker run -p 3000:3000 autodesk-assignment-api
The API should now be accessible at http://localhost:3000.

